>> Well, in my view--

00:36:31.810 --> 00:36:33.160 align:middle line:90%
and it's not just my view.

00:36:33.160 --> 00:36:35.080 align:middle line:90%
It's about us waking up.

00:36:35.080 --> 00:36:37.030 align:middle line:84%
It's about us waking
up and literally

00:36:37.030 --> 00:36:39.670 align:middle line:84%
remembering who we
really are and the deeper

00:36:39.670 --> 00:36:40.970 align:middle line:90%
nature of reality.

00:36:40.970 --> 00:36:42.760 align:middle line:90%
So it's waking up.

00:36:42.760 --> 00:36:48.910 align:middle line:84%
It's growing up because this is
a very empowering understanding,

00:36:48.910 --> 00:36:55.180 align:middle line:84%
but it calls us, it invites us
to step into that empowerment

00:36:55.180 --> 00:37:03.280 align:middle line:84%
and to accept our responsibility
joyously as co-creators

00:37:03.280 --> 00:37:06.070 align:middle line:84%
of our realities and,
therefore, responsibility

00:37:06.070 --> 00:37:09.840 align:middle line:84%
for how we are in the
world and with the world.

00:37:09.840 --> 00:37:11.720 align:middle line:90%
And then we can clean up.

00:37:11.720 --> 00:37:14.570 align:middle line:84%
We can clean up all
the traumas that

00:37:14.570 --> 00:37:17.990 align:middle line:84%
have come alongside the
luggage, the baggage, that

00:37:17.990 --> 00:37:23.120 align:middle line:84%
have come alongside with this
misunderstanding and this buy-in

00:37:23.120 --> 00:37:27.860 align:middle line:84%
to the myth of separation,
which is fairly modern.

00:37:27.860 --> 00:37:31.640 align:middle line:84%
It really has grown
to an extreme level

00:37:31.640 --> 00:37:35.980 align:middle line:84%
in the last few hundred
and even the last 50 years.

00:37:35.980 --> 00:37:40.010 align:middle line:84%
So we haven't been having this
worldview, this fragmentation

00:37:40.010 --> 00:37:41.180 align:middle line:90%
for the whole of humanity.

00:37:41.180 --> 00:37:43.280 align:middle line:90%
It's incredibly recent.

00:37:43.280 --> 00:37:46.940 align:middle line:84%
And in one sense, it's
helpful for the technology.

00:37:46.940 --> 00:37:49.880 align:middle line:84%
But in an infinitely
more profound way,

00:37:49.880 --> 00:37:54.110 align:middle line:84%
it's been a huge disservice
for our evolution

00:37:54.110 --> 00:37:57.110 align:middle line:84%
and for the evolution
of our relationship

00:37:57.110 --> 00:37:59.780 align:middle line:84%
with Mother Earth
and the cosmos.

00:37:59.780 --> 00:38:04.046 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, if it's so recent,
at what point was it--

00:38:04.046 --> 00:38:05.210 align:middle line:90%
was it religion?

00:38:05.210 --> 00:38:06.440 align:middle line:90%
Was it government?

00:38:06.440 --> 00:38:10.550 align:middle line:84%
At what point did
it begin to emerge,

00:38:10.550 --> 00:38:15.200 align:middle line:84%
this new concept, this
materialistic reductionism?

00:38:15.200 --> 00:38:18.170 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, really, it probably
goes back about 300 years

00:38:18.170 --> 00:38:19.880 align:middle line:90%
to the time of Isaac Newton.

00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:24.140 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, the
Church had huge authority.

00:38:24.140 --> 00:38:26.270 align:middle line:84%
And there were a
number of what's

00:38:26.270 --> 00:38:28.910 align:middle line:90%
called natural philosophers.

00:38:28.910 --> 00:38:30.410 align:middle line:84%
They weren't called
scientists then.

00:38:30.410 --> 00:38:31.952 align:middle line:84%
They were called
natural philosophers

00:38:31.952 --> 00:38:37.010 align:middle line:84%
who wanted to understand the
world not just through religion

00:38:37.010 --> 00:38:39.870 align:middle line:84%
but through experiment
and testing.

00:38:39.870 --> 00:38:43.520 align:middle line:84%
And so the scientific
method was born of saying,

00:38:43.520 --> 00:38:44.637 align:middle line:90%
I will research this.

00:38:44.637 --> 00:38:45.470 align:middle line:90%
I will look at this.

00:38:45.470 --> 00:38:48.150 align:middle line:84%
I will find out more about
it through experiment.

00:38:48.150 --> 00:38:51.060 align:middle line:90%
And so there came a deal.

00:38:51.060 --> 00:38:53.330 align:middle line:84%
There was a real deal between
the natural philosophers

00:38:53.330 --> 00:38:55.490 align:middle line:90%
and the religious authorities.

00:38:55.490 --> 00:38:57.290 align:middle line:84%
The religious
authorities would look

00:38:57.290 --> 00:39:00.620 align:middle line:84%
after the souls of everyone,
and the natural philosophers

00:39:00.620 --> 00:39:04.490 align:middle line:84%
were OK as long as they just
looked at the physical world.

00:39:04.490 --> 00:39:07.940 align:middle line:84%
And that became very--
it was very sensible

00:39:07.940 --> 00:39:12.230 align:middle line:84%
because if you weren't
willing to just research

00:39:12.230 --> 00:39:14.390 align:middle line:84%
the physical world
as a scientist,

00:39:14.390 --> 00:39:17.660 align:middle line:84%
you were potentially under house
arrest for the rest of your life

00:39:17.660 --> 00:39:21.800 align:middle line:84%
as a heretic as Galileo was,
or you were burnt at the stake

00:39:21.800 --> 00:39:23.450 align:middle line:90%
like Giordano Bruno was.

00:39:23.450 --> 00:39:26.000 align:middle line:84%
So it was a pretty
dangerous thing

00:39:26.000 --> 00:39:29.300 align:middle line:84%
to not just keep to your
little bit of research.

00:39:29.300 --> 00:39:32.720 align:middle line:84%
But it creates a schism,
and that schism just grew.

00:39:32.720 --> 00:39:35.990 align:middle line:84%
And so scientists
began to denigrate

00:39:35.990 --> 00:39:38.270 align:middle line:90%
religion and spirituality.

00:39:38.270 --> 00:39:41.330 align:middle line:84%
And spirituality
kept on its track.

00:39:41.330 --> 00:39:46.430 align:middle line:84%
So the two just separated
literally in their worldviews.

00:39:46.430 --> 00:39:51.060 align:middle line:84%
And science was
very, very powerful.

00:39:51.060 --> 00:39:53.300 align:middle line:84%
It brought us the
Industrial Revolution.

00:39:53.300 --> 00:39:55.310 align:middle line:84%
It brought us--
well, first of all,

00:39:55.310 --> 00:39:57.380 align:middle line:84%
the Enlightenment, the
Industrial Revolution,

00:39:57.380 --> 00:39:58.190 align:middle line:90%
and on and on.

00:39:58.190 --> 00:40:00.590 align:middle line:84%
It brought us all
the technologies

00:40:00.590 --> 00:40:03.200 align:middle line:84%
that make our lives
so much easier today.

00:40:03.200 --> 00:40:09.640 align:middle line:84%
But its basic premise was that
this material realm, this realm,

00:40:09.640 --> 00:40:11.600 align:middle line:90%
this universe, is all there is.

00:40:11.600 --> 00:40:13.540 align:middle line:84%
There are no other
realms beyond it.

00:40:13.540 --> 00:40:17.440 align:middle line:84%
Its appearance of separation
is its true reality

00:40:17.440 --> 00:40:20.980 align:middle line:84%
that our universe is
essentially an accident,

00:40:20.980 --> 00:40:24.250 align:middle line:84%
that evolution
proceeds by accidents,

00:40:24.250 --> 00:40:29.770 align:middle line:84%
that after a long, long, long
time, human beings emerged,

00:40:29.770 --> 00:40:32.890 align:middle line:84%
evolved, and somehow
our consciousness

00:40:32.890 --> 00:40:37.090 align:middle line:84%
arises from our
material brains somehow.

00:40:37.090 --> 00:40:38.800 align:middle line:90%
That was the story.

00:40:38.800 --> 00:40:45.010 align:middle line:84%
So it's a story of separation,
of accident, of meaninglessness,

00:40:45.010 --> 00:40:46.460 align:middle line:90%
and it's wrong.

00:40:46.460 --> 00:40:47.780 align:middle line:90%
It's utterly wrong.

00:40:47.780 --> 00:40:51.280 align:middle line:84%
So we're now realizing through
the leading-edge science

00:40:51.280 --> 00:40:54.400 align:middle line:84%
evidence that it is
fundamentally wrong

00:40:54.400 --> 00:41:00.040 align:middle line:84%
and that instead mind and
matter are essentially

00:41:00.040 --> 00:41:03.280 align:middle line:84%
one, that mind expresses itself
as what we call energy, matter,

00:41:03.280 --> 00:41:07.640 align:middle line:84%
and spacetime, and that mind
and consciousness are something

00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:10.880 align:middle line:84%
we have, that what we
and the whole world are,

00:41:10.880 --> 00:41:17.630 align:middle line:84%
and that our universe exists and
evolves both as a unified entity

00:41:17.630 --> 00:41:20.120 align:middle line:84%
and with meaning
and with purpose

00:41:20.120 --> 00:41:23.390 align:middle line:84%
because it's so
exquisitely set up.

00:41:23.390 --> 00:41:28.370 align:middle line:84%
It literally exists to
evolve from simplicity

00:41:28.370 --> 00:41:32.870 align:middle line:84%
to complexity and
ever-greater levels

00:41:32.870 --> 00:41:35.960 align:middle line:90%
of individuated self-awareness.

00:41:35.960 --> 00:41:40.460 align:middle line:84%
It's a universe that
is innately intelligent

00:41:40.460 --> 00:41:42.860 align:middle line:84%
but, like a human
being growing up,

00:41:42.860 --> 00:41:46.280 align:middle line:84%
learns to know
itself and experience

00:41:46.280 --> 00:41:48.360 align:middle line:90%
the world in that way.

00:41:48.360 --> 00:41:51.500 align:middle line:84%
And it's a world
not of separation.

00:41:51.500 --> 00:41:56.400 align:middle line:84%
It's a world of unity
